{
  "text": "In the Verdegay approach, only the return constraint has been fuzzified, and the objective function has been bound indirectly to the fuzzy return constraint via a variable, y t . Calculations should be carried out repeatedly for different satisfaction levels. However, because of the fuzzy constraint, Eq. (15), in M4, the objective function should be fuzzified as well [CITATION_1] . Moreover, the objective in real life is to determine an \u03b1, which provides optimum satisfaction for different risk and return combinations simultaneously. This determination can be made via the Werners approach [CITATION_2] .",
